        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "prefix": 1.0,
                "text": "Introduction"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 18
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 2019.0,
                "text": "This document sets out the policy for the holding of reserves held in the Mid and South Hospitals Charity (MSE Charity) as required by the Charity Commission Statement of Recommended Practice (SORP)"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 19
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "prefix": 2.0,
                "text": "Scope"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 20
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 2.1,
                "text": "Trustees are under a legal duty to apply charity funds within a reasonable time of receiving them. This document aims to set out:"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 21
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "The reasons why the charity holds reserves."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 22
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "What level of reserves the trustee believes the charity needs."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 23
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "Arrangements for maintaining reserves at the agreed level."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 24
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "Monitoring and review of policy arrangements."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 25
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "prefix": 3.0,
                "text": "Definitions"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 26
        },
        {
            "type": "table",
            "sequence_num": 27,
            "data": {
                "num_rows": 8,
                "num_cols": 2,
                "table_items": [
                    {
                        "text": "Term"
                    },
                    {
                        "text": "Definition"
                    },
                    {
                        "text": "Charitable Funds Committee"
                    },
                    {
                        "text": "Subcommittee of the Corporate Trustee for Mid and South Essex Hospitals Charity which has devolved responsibility for the ongoing management of funds. The committee consists of any four members of the Corporate Trustee (excluding the Chief Finance Officer ), made up of members of the Board of Directors for Mid and South Essex NHS Foundation Trust and is supported by the Foundation Trust Secretary and representatives from the Charity and the Finance Department."
                    },
                    {
                        "text": "Corporate Trustee"
                    },
                    {
                        "text": "The Trustee of Mid and South Essex Hospitals Charity is the corporate body Mid and South Essex NHS Foundation Trust."
                    },
                    {
                        "text": "Designated Fund"
                    },
                    {
                        "text": "A designated fund constitutes unrestricted fund monies that have been allocated by the Corporate Trustee for a particular purpose (also known as PC/Trust Fund). This is for administrative purposes only and does not legally restrict Trustees' discretion to apply the monies in this way."
                    },
                    {
                        "text": "Endowment Fund"
                    },
                    {
                        "text": "There are two types of endowment fund, one is a permanent endowment fund which the charity cannot spend as income, it must be invested to produce income for the charity which is then spent in accordance with the purpose of the charity or used in the activities of the charity. The other type is an expendable endowment fund, which can be spent but differs from donated income as there is no requirement to spend the capital until the Trustee wishes to. Until then it must be invested to create income which is then spent for the purposes of the charity within a reasonable amount of time."
                    },
                    {
                        "text": "Fund Manager"
                    },
                    {
                        "text": "A fund manager is the person approved by the Charitable Funds Committee to have delegated responsibility as outlined in the Trust's Standing Financial Instructions and Scheme of Delegation."
                    },
                    {
                        "text": "General Purpose Fund"
                    },
                    {
                        "text": "A fund that holds unrestricted monies which have not been earmarked by the Corporate Trustee."
                    },
                    {
                        "text": "Governing"
                    },
                    {
                        "text": "This document is required to establish the terms and objects (purpose) of a"
                    }
                ]
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "table",
            "sequence_num": 28,
            "data": {
                "num_rows": 4,
                "num_cols": 2,
                "table_items": [
                    {
                        "text": "Document"
                    },
                    {
                        "text": "charity. It is combined with a registration document to formally register a charity with the Charity Commission."
                    },
                    {
                        "text": "Legacy"
                    },
                    {
                        "text": "Money or property bequeathed to the charity in a will."
                    },
                    {
                        "text": "Restricted Fund"
                    },
                    {
                        "text": "A fund that holds income and/or capital which can only be applied for specific purposes. The restriction will be imposed by the donor at the point of donation."
                    },
                    {
                        "text": "Unrestricted Fund"
                    },
                    {
                        "text": "An Unrestricted Fund is one that can be spent at the Trustee's discretion in furtherance of the charity's objectives."
                    }
                ]
            }
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "prefix": 4.0,
                "text": "Role and responsibilities within the Trust"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 29
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 4.1,
                "text": "Role of the Finance Department"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 30
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "The following mechanisms are in place to ensure proper management of funds to ensure the desired reserves levels are met:"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 31
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "Operational guidance provided to Trust staff publicising the availability of charitable funds and outlining the obligations for spending of funds in a timely and responsible manner."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 32
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "Provide reports to the Charitable Funds Committee to enable them to monitor the funds to ensure reserves are held and maintained at the levels agreed, reporting any issues to the Trustee."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 33
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "prefix": 5.0,
                "text": "Reserves policy"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 34
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 5.1,
                "text": "The Corporate Trustee formulates the reserves policy in accordance with the Charity Commission booklet CC19, Charities' Reserves."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 35
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 5.2,
                "text": "Reserves are that part of a charity's unrestricted funds that is freely available to spend on any of the charity's purposes after taking account of designated funds that have been earmarked for specific projects."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 36
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 5.3,
                "text": "The Corporate Trustee has a minimum target for reserves of \u00a3500,000 which is required for the continued administration of the charity and has a ceiling for reserves of \u00a35,000,000. The minimum level of reserves is equivalent to 1 year administration and support costs for the charity plus an estimate of winding down costs. The proposed fund ceiling equates to 2 years expenditure. Any unrestricted funds above the minimum target allows the Corporate Trustee the freedom to make grants when they are needed in anticipation of donations, whilst being mindful of guidance from the Charity Commission that donations should be spent within two to three years of receipt."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 37
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 5.4,
                "text": "The Corporate Trustee anticipates that maintaining the target level of reserves is likely to be achievable given the level of unrestricted funds held. The Charitable Funds Committee reviews compliance with this policy at each meeting. The Corporate Trustee notes the level of designated funds within the charity and has"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 38
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "plans to continue to spend these balances on the areas appropriate to donor's wishes."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 39
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 5.5,
                "text": "In the event that the need identified for any designated funds no longer exists or the designated fund has been inactive for more than five years, these funds will be closed and transferred to the general purpose fund."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 40
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "prefix": 6.0,
                "text": "Training requirements"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 41
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 6.1,
                "text": "No specific training requirements."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 42
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "prefix": 7.0,
                "text": "Monitoring and audit"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 43
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 7.1,
                "text": "Outlined below is the Trust's process of monitoring compliance with, and the effectiveness of the document's main points."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 44
        },
